@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}

<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>Email Blaster</h1>
    <p class="lead">Open source Asp.net MVC 5 web application for sending email blasts using SendGrid platform</p>
    <p>First things first, open web.config and update the following:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>1. Replace the ConnectionString with the Username and Password to initialize the EmailBlaster SQL Database. <small>(It is assumed that you already created the SQL Server User login with dbcreator role)</small></li>
        <li>2. Replace SendgridAPIKey with your own SendGrid key. <small>(It is assumed that you have already have an account, paid or non-paid, in SendGrid and know your assigned API keys)</small></li>
        <li>3. Open Nuget Console and type: UPDATE-DATABASE</li>
        <li>4. Compile and Run application and 
            <a href="/Contact/CreateBulk" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Start Adding Contacts &raquo;</a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
